p://pages.cthome.net/shellene/june/water_bar.jpg class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ubaahlipurpleeyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baahli Purple Eyes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#330000>(3/24/02 8:02:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus Items and you</span><hr size=1> <br>
Instant universal upgrade requiring no effort on the players part without a retune of the mobs to compensate = a big deal. Right around luclin release, resists on DD's were lowered and the day of luclin release all casters got a large boost to their mana pool. BOOM, AoW dead across 50 servers for their first time ever. Are you trying to tell me that's a coincidence? My entire point is that giving players a FREE upgrade in power without empowering the mobs to compensate ALWAYS breaks the game. I could list a few thousand precedents in EQ alone if you want. <br>
<br>
This isnt the only upgrade casters have recieved either:<br>
Flowing thought 15, innate mana regen 3, KEI = more than double the standing mana regen you had one expansion ago -nevermind crits and various other AA skills.. Our wizards are the key to half the encounters we do now - ssra mobs with uber ac, ae'ing the ring of worm, ring of CT, ring of acrylia, ring around the collar... On top of that, mobs have AC so high we may as well be wielding summoned daggers. <br>
<br>
Not to mention Bane spells in Ntov and other places.<br>
<br>
my entire point is that normally with focus items you get a huge damage upgrade, that kind of damage upgrade for an entire guild would come in months of farming other mobs to prepare for the bigger encounter. Instead that damage upgrade came overnight assuming that guild had 4pp to spare for one of their mages.<br>
<br>
and that my friend is unbalancing.<br>
<br>
