<br>
Let's outline the upgrades casters have recieved according to Zazess.<br>
<br>
- Flowing Thought 15: Pretty laughable upgrade since no one is probably even close to reaching this threshold. It's like saying melee's can be hasted to up to 200% but never implement items for them to get there.<br>
- KEI: very nice spell but you could already have those benefits, you just needed more spells cast on you rather than just one. Save buffs slots and longer lasting.<br>
- Innate mana regen 3: Requires a minumum of 18 AA points and level 55+. Maybe 2% of all active wizards of all levels have this skill.<br>
- Crits: Requires a minumum of 18 AA points and level 59+. Maybe 5% of all active wizards have this AA skill (being optimistic with the 5%).<br>
- High AC mobs: Welcome to the world of resists casters have experienced for the past 3 years. Tastes a little bitter when you don't feel like pulling your own weight in terms of damage. This has been a caster's pain since the release of Kunark.<br>
- AE: Is what wizards do best but yet it is a highly specialized skill. Rare occurrence that any wizard will ever experience AE.<br>
- Bane spells: The best mana/damage ratio spell a wizard has in their arsenal. Very situational spell as well and not very many wizards will ever get to use a bane spell. The two dots per cast cost is also very rediculous.<br>
<br>
In implementing a piece of caster balance through summoned focus items, Verant is able to add power to the entire casting community. Casters have recieved little to no upgrades in their spell lines as each expansion was released. An Ice Comet today is the same as the Ice Comet of day one. Well, maybe a wizard in today's age can cast one more Ice Comet per bar of mana.<br>
<br>
QuikPick Emberlore<br>
Sorceress of Crimson Watchers<br>
