Dest<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uleavandoreq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LeavandorEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Advocate<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 317<br> <font color=#330000>(3/25/02 10:44:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> The only fault VI had in this scenario is that they put the changes out before they truly thought everything over, and seeing as how the Test server doesn't have an adequate population to test every single aspect of every single change they implement, things like th CHeal thing can get past.<br>
<br>
VI did a good thing in nerfing that, no matter what mage says what, I still want a challenge in the end-game.  I'm not saying I don't want to see a mage wanted/needed at raids, I'm saying that this one particular change did change the entire game and its very fine balance issues.<br>
<br>
There are so many things that VI has implemented in the past months that have made the high end game 50% easier than it was before.  First and foremost, AA skills.  The threshold on these skills still isn't met, and people will be reaching the point that they were at during the final months of Kunark.  But a lot quicker this time.<br>
<br>
I would bet that if this change this unbalancing were imposed on Enchanters (of whom are required at any raid of the guild's level) and then nerfed, there wouldn't be near the same uprising.  Even though the same changes would have been made.  The only reason this is reaching such levels of discontent is that a nerf was aimed at a class that was already upset at the nerfs they have recieved.<br>
<br>
The idea is superb, but in practice the pre-nerf changes were horribly unbalancing to the sanctity of EQ's high-end game. <p><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=1><tr><td bgcolor=#006600 width=225 height=26><font color=#FFFF00 size=-2 face=arial><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12010"><font color=#FFFFFF size=-2 face=arial>Leavandor Sires</font></a>, 59th Beguiler<br> Husband to Corinna Sires, 60th Phantasmist</font><td>
<td bgcolor=#006600 width=225><font color=#FFFF00 size=-2 face=arial><font size=-2 face=arial><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=89128"><font color=#FFFFFF size=-2 face=arial>Vinadir V`Seer</font></a>, 59th Templar<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67807"><font color=#FFFFFF size=-2 face=arial>Krabluk Frogbarsh</font></a>, 59th Myrmidon<tr><td height=13 colspan=3><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><td width=175><font size=-2 face=arial></font><td bgcolor=#006600 width=100><center><a href="http://www.geocities.com/eqgrubs"><font color=#FFFFFF size=-2 face=arial>The Grubs</font></a></center><td width=175><font size=-2 face=arial> </font></table></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uscrubfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>scrubfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#330000>(3/25/02 10:52:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I think people will soon forget the mage summoned items over dropped items for a few reasons:<br>
<br>
- Poor statistics.  The max stats the mage focus items have are 20 hp and 20 mana.  And that's for 50+ level spells.  Expect the dropped items to have much nicer statistics.<br>
<br>
- Lower percentage focus:  The maximum item haste is what... around 40%?  I think you can resonable expect the higher end focus items to be a vast improvement over the summoned items.<br>
<br>
- Different types of focus:  The mage focus items only have 5 types of focus, and there are restrictions on all those effects.  The ring has spell delay restriction, the earring only reduces mana on DD's, the shoulders only increases buff duration on self.  How valuable would a focus item be if it increased the duration on all buffs?  How about one that increased the duration of a DoT?  Alan has hinted at different types of focus, so I think it's reasonable to expect that the mage items are just a preview for what's to come. <p>--------------------------<BR>
