 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uvylle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vylle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#330000>(3/25/02 11:42:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Why do people bitch when another class gets something that makes the game more enjoyable?  I don't understand this, and is the hight of selfishness IMO.<br>
<br>
I play several characters, the highest of which are a 51 Nec and 52 Cleric.  I know I am not 'uber' by any stretch of the imagination, and so because I am not uber I cannot speak of the High-end game which AL / LotD take part in.<br>
<br>
But that is ok with me... I play to have fun, and fun to me is hanging out with in-game and RL friends... whether that be in an EXP group somewhere or doing a raid or epic encounter.<br>
<br>
If another class gets something that improves their class then I am pleased... chances are that their improvement will benefit everyone in a group.  When mage focus items were introduced I thought to myself 'Wow' 'what a great idea!'.  Doing this for the mage wasn't simply doing it for the Mage class... it was an ability for the Mage to Improve ALL Casters!!<br>
<br>
I can't think of a better improvement that could have been done.  And to complain about it is pretty lame. <p><p><b>Vylle Lifestealer</b> - Heretic<BR>
<A href='http://www.council.allhell.com'>Council of the Forgotten</A><BR>
<img src=http://www.council.allhell.com/vyllesig.jpg
> <br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukopla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kopla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#330000>(3/25/02 12:37:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Most people have posted some very good arguements.  I can see merit in both sides, but with having a caster bias I have to lean towards Natan and Dest's side.  <br>
<br>
The nerf to focus item effects on CH was a good thing, that I see.  But what many people are not realizing is the focus items did not improve damage done by a caster by 20%.  Now I don't know what kind of effect the speed increase would have on damage output, but the increased DD dmg bracer is no where near 20%.  It is variable.  Watch it long enough and you will quickly see it averages about a 10% increase.  <br>
<br>
Now I only see 1 problem with the ease of acquiring these items.  Dropped upgrades, unless made rather disappointing, would quickly inflate these numbers to a unblancing proportion.<br>
<br>
Taken without thought of the future, these summoned focus items are currently not unbalancing.  They do not trivialize content, for the big raids they make it so instead of a mage, you have the damage output of another monk if you added all of the casters together.<br>
<br>
Overall, because it is such a marginal difference, people's opinion of this will be on the side of their main character's bias.<br>
Kopla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uthedrunkenmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Drunken Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#330000>(3/25/02 2:27:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=60>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Nobody knows about how the dropped items are going to work... So I think it is premature to say that people won't want the real ones because it is easier to just get one from a mage.  After three years of summoning useless shit, I am CONFIDENT that the mage summoned items will be crap compared to the real thing :)  Heck, maybe they'll even stack like FT items (with a reasonable cap somewhere).<br>
<br>
I think that the higher level focus item spells should have been monster drops instead of vendor purchased.<br>
<br>
I still don't see why people think these are any different than melee buffs... take the damage output of any tank with and without chanter haste and do the comparison.<br>
<br>
I do think that fast CHeals would be unbalancing, unless they come from a very rare and difficult to obtain item.  So make focus items so they do not affect heals unless specifically flagged to do so... and make those items uber caster loot from boss mobs.  Problem solved.<br>
<br>
Other than the heals... I still don't think these items do anything to overall balance.<br>
<br>
As for people leaving corpses so they can keep their focus items... I would MUCH rather be able to cast a buff spell than summon an item to hand to someone... but VI's &quot;vision&quot; for mages is that we make items.  I think a good comprimise would be to have the items be charged... with enough charges to be useful but not so many that people can keep it forever.  Maybe have the effect last for 2 minutes after you click it... and give it 30 charges.  An hour of continuous use wouldn't be out of line with other buffs, and it would still let it fall into the &quot;masters of summoning crap&quot; storyline for mages.  I just know that ever since release, this is the FIRST time mages have had an item that people of the mage's level will even consider wearing.  We used to have three useful summons... EB stones (nobody uses 'em anymore, eb items are very easy to get), levitation rings, and mod rods.  Now VI has finally added another line of gear that people actually want.  Kind of a nice thing for a mage.<br>
<br>
And if summoning these items makes me a &quot;focus item bitch&quot; then I guess we could call druids &quot;circle buff and sow bitches&quot; and shammys &quot;buff bitches.&quot;  I'd rather be a focus item bitch that does something useful on a raid, than a mage sitting in Seb or Velks LFG 'cause nobody wants/needs me on a raid.<br>
